2012 Privacy Policy This Website is run by Patient.co.uk .
Patient.co.uk is a brand name of Egton Medical Information Systems Limited , a company registered in England with company number 2117205 with registered offices at Rawdon House , Green Lane , Yeadon , Leeds , LS19 7BY .
Patient.co.uk operates by the following principles : We do our best to protect your personal details and other information about your account .
We are constantly reviewing our processes and procedures to protect your personal information from unauthorised access and use , accidental loss and/or destruction .
We will respect your privacy .
You should receive marketing emails only from Patient.co.uk .
It will be made clear to you where you have these choices , for example , tick boxes will let you decide whether you wish to receive marketing or newsletters .
We may , however , email you occasionally with information or queries about your registration , your subscription account , your Website activity or postings , for example , with reminders , confirmations , warnings or copyright requests .
Sometimes we use other organisations to process your personal information on our behalf .
Such processing shall comply with appropriate security measures .
We may also independently audit these service providers to ensure that they meet our standards .
We may use service providers to help us run the Website or services available on the Website , some of whom may be based outside the EEA .
We explicitly ask when we need information that personally identifies you ( " Personal Information " ) .
For example , when you register with the Patient.co.uk discussion forums you are asked for an e-mail address , password and nickname .
We may use technology to track the patterns of behaviour of visitors to our site .
This can include using a " cookie " which would be stored on your browser .
You can modify your browser to prevent this happening .
The information collected in this way can be used to identify you unless you modify your browser settings .
For more information on cookies and to learn how to change your settings , read our cookie policy .
If at any time you believe that Patient.co.uk has not adhered to these principles , please notify us by e-mail to the webmaster , and we will use all commercially reasonable efforts to determine and correct the problem promptly .
